From: Felipe Balbi <balbi@ti.com>
Date: Fri, 28 Aug 2015 16:14:40 -0500
Subject: [PATCH 544/800] usb: dwc3: core: re-sync FSM inputs on resume

This sorts out cases where USB cable is dettached
while we're still suspended.

Signed-off-by: Felipe Balbi <balbi@ti.com>
Signed-off-by: Sekhar Nori <nsekhar@ti.com>
[zou: Original patch taken from PROCESSOR-SDK-LINUX-AM335X 02_00_01_07]
Signed-off-by: zou cao <cao.zou@windriver.com>
---
 drivers/usb/dwc3/core.c |    1 +
 1 files changed, 1 insertions(+), 0 deletions(-)

diff --git a/drivers/usb/dwc3/core.c b/drivers/usb/dwc3/core.c
index aefe13a..13db777 100644
--- a/drivers/usb/dwc3/core.c
+++ b/drivers/usb/dwc3/core.c
@@ -1671,6 +1671,7 @@ static int dwc3_resume(struct device *dev)
 		dwc3_writel(dwc->regs, DWC3_OCFG, dwc->ocfg);
 		dwc3_writel(dwc->regs, DWC3_OCTL, dwc->octl);
 		dwc3_otg_unmask_irq(dwc);
+		dwc3_otg_fsm_sync(dwc);
 	}
 	spin_unlock_irqrestore(&dwc->lock, flags);
 
